[00:01.69]Lesson 3
[00:02.90]Please send me a card
[00:04.87]First listen and then answer the question:
[00:09.68]How many cards did the writer send?
[00:16.07]Postcards always spoil my holidays.
[00:19.99]Last summer,I went to Italy.I visited museums and sat in public gardens.
[00:29.23]A friendly waiter taught me a few words of Italian.Then he lent me a book.
[00:36.67]I read a few lines,but I did not understand a word.
[00:43.07]Every day I thought about postcards.
[00:45.48]My holidays passed quickly,but I did not send cards to my friends.
[00:51.99]On the last day I made a big decision.I got up early and bought thirty-seven cards.
[01:02.49]I spent the whole day in my room,but I did not write a single card!
